    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There's multiple workarounds at least for this case:\r\n\r\n1. wrap the input in the label and you don't need the brittle coupling of ids, which is more accessible\r\n2. use `transformData` as you said\r\n3. we add `attributeName` to all of the templates\r\n\r\nI can see why you'd want this, but we haven't had any problems so far with this, so I'm not sure yet if it should be added.\r\n\r\nIf you have a lot of toggles, is it possible you really want a custom [refinementList](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html) instead? That would be simpler I think. You can customise the rendering completely by using the connector if necessary",
